Telecom Segment: â€¢)The company( jio-Telecom segment ) registered a significant improvement led by the addition of 29 million subscribers, higher data consumption due to 5G adoption, and a 3% improvement in ARPU.  Retail Segment: â€¢)Revenues grew by 20% driven by a rapid expansion in the retail space area, while revenue per square feet continued to be moderate.  â€¢)The Grocery business led the growth by 59% YoY growth in the Smart and the Smart Bazaars.  â€¢)The Fashion and lifestyle business grew 15% YoY, driven by a pick-up in store traffic as well as average bill value.   â€¢)The digital and new commerce business( jio Mart & Ajio ) continued to grow contributing 18% of the revenues.  Conclusion: Performance of legacy businesses ( O2C Segment )was Slow down in Q1 FY24 and the new-age businesses, such as retail, media, digital, and renewables, would continue to drive the Business Growth.

#JioFinancialServices : All you need to know about the spin-off  ğŸ“… Record date: The record date for the spin-off is July 20. This means that any shareholder who holds shares in #Reliance Industries on this date will be eligible to receive shares in Jio Financial Services.  âš–ï¸ Ratio: The ratio of shares is 1:1, meaning that for every share of Reliance Industries held, shareholders will receive one share of Jio Financial Services.  ğŸ“¢ Special session: The #NSE will hold a special pre-open session on July 20 to determine the price discovery of the two new entities. The price of Jio Financial Services will be set at a discount to the price of Reliance Industries.  ğŸ“ˆ #Nifty: Jio Financial Services will be included in the #Nifty50 as its 51st stock. It will stay there at a constant price until it is listed, and then it will be removed from the Nifty.  ğŸ’° Market valuation: The market is valuing Jio Financial Services at Rs 160-200 per share, based on its treasury stock. However, the company has not yet released any growth targets or projections, so the market valuation is still uncertain.
